    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h1><em>java.time</em></h1>\n<p>Never use the legacy classes <code>Date</code> and <code>SimpleDateFormat</code>. Use only <em>java.time</em> classes.</p>\n<pre><code>DateTimeFormatter f = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern( &quot;MM/dd/uuuu&quot; ) ;\nLocalDate ld = LocalDate.parse( input , f ) ;\n</code></pre>\n<p>To add and subtract, call the <code>plus…</code> and <code>minus…</code> methods.</p>\n<pre><code>LocalDate later = ld.plusDays( 3 ) ;\nLocalDate earlier = ld.minusYears( 7 ) ;\n</code></pre>\n"
