  "title" : "How do I take date as input in Java and be able to add/subtract its days/months/years",
  "body" : "<p>I'm currently using this code and I don't know if there is a way to add or subtract the date that I input with <code>Scanner(System.in)</code></p>\n<pre><code>Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\nSystem.out.println(&quot;Date: &quot;);\nString date = scanner.next();\nSimpleDateFormat dateFormat = new SimpleDateFormat(&quot;MM/dd/yyyy&quot;);\nDate date2=null;\ntry {\n    date2 = dateFormat.parse(date);\n} catch (ParseException e) {\n    e.printStackTrace();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
